<title>
    APIs at the Library of Congress | Library of Congress
</title>
<meta name="dc.title"
        content="APIs at the Library of Congress | Library of Congress">
<meta property="og:title"
        content="APIs at the Library of Congress | Library of Congress">
    <meta name='description' content=' 
    This site
    describes how the Library makes information available via a series of
    application programming interfaces (APIs). Specifically, it includes technical
    documentation of the Library&#39;s loc.gov JSON API, its sitemaps, and suite of microservices.
    If you&#39;re looking for non-computational ways to access digital materials online, the Guide to Digital Scholarship at the Library of Congress and the
    Using the Library of Congress Online Guide for Middle and High School Students provide strategies for searching the digital collections.
'>
    <meta property="og:description" content=" 
    This site
    describes how the Library makes information available via a series of
    application programming interfaces (APIs). Specifically, it includes technical
    documentation of the Library&#39;s loc.gov JSON API, its sitemaps, and suite of microservices.
    If you&#39;re looking for non-computational ways to access digital materials online, the Guide to Digital Scholarship at the Library of Congress and the
    Using the Library of Congress Online Guide for Middle and High School Students provide strategies for searching the digital collections.
">

